the exceedingly Italian Tito
Belcredi (John Koch), Lady
Matilde and her daughter (Mari
Pappas and Lori Sharpless)
and the slick Carlo di Nolli
(Shawn Ebbert). Enrico expati-
ates about the meanings of
words and how labels are
uniquely interpreted by both
the speaker and the listener in
the midst of being psychologi-
cally dissected by the doctor
and Belcredi. He voices many
Futurist and modernist ideas
dealing with death and its com-

 

   

 

